'''Faye Morton''' is the name of a fictional character in the [[BBC]] television series [[Holby City]].<ref name="character">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/drama/holbycity/characters/profiles/index.shtml?content/_faye/page1|title=Holby City - Characters|publisher=[[BBC.co.uk]]|accessdate=2007-08-11}}</ref>  The character is portrayed by actress [[Patsy Kensit]].<ref name="patsy">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/4527980.stm|title=Patsy Kensit to join Holby cast|date=[[14 December]] [[2005]]|publisher=[[BBC.co.uk]]|accessdate=2007-08-11}}</ref>  Her first appearance in the show occurred on [[30 January]] [[2007 in television|2007]] in episode ''Into the Dark'' - [[List_of_Holby_City_episodes/Series_Nine#Series_Nine_.282006-2007.29|Series 9]], Episode 17 of the programme.<ref name="joined">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/drama/holbycity/storyupdates/index.shtml?20070130|title=Episode Update Tuesday 30th Jan|publisher=[[BBC.co.uk]]|date=[[30 January]] [[2007]]|accessdate=2007-08-11}}</ref> Her role in the show is that of the mysterious [[femme fatale]] - seemingly meek and shy but with a murderous past.  The character's introductory storyline (shot on location in [[Dubai]]) which saw her kill her husband and calmly walk away, proved so popular that Kensit was shortlisted ''Best Actress'' in the [[2007]] [[TV Quick]] and TV Choice Awards for her portrayal of the character, within just three months of arriving on the show.<ref name="award">{{cite web|url=http://web.archive.org/web/20070524095225/http://www.tvchoiceawards.co.uk/|title=2007 TV Quick & TV Choice Awards|publisher=[[TV Quick]]|date=[[May]] [[2007]]|accessdate=2007-08-11}}</ref>
